# VBA Source File Rules

When editing VBA source files (`.bas`, `.cls`) or Access SaveAsText files (`.form`, `.report`, `.qdef`, `.macro`), follow these rules:

## File Structure - Do NOT Modify

- `Attribute VB_Name` line - must match filename without extension
- `VERSION 1.0 CLASS` / `BEGIN` / `END` blocks in class files
- Module-level `Attribute VB_*` lines

## Safe to Modify

- VBA code (procedures, functions, properties)
- Comment headers and documentation
- Member attribute descriptions (text in quotes)

## Coding Standards

- Include procedure headers with Author, Date, Purpose
- Use `Option Compare Database` and `Option Explicit`
- Follow naming conventions: `str*`, `lng*`, `bln*`, `d*` (Dictionary), `c*` (class objects)
- Use `T()` function for translatable strings

